byline.contributor: Carl Hulse contributed reporting from Washington, and Jim Rutenberg from Philadelphia.

abstract: New analysis; Pres Obama’s foreign policy successes have bolstered his credentials as a strong wartime leader, but the 2012 presidential election is likely to be dominated by the economy and job market.
